  "texts": [
    "Placing the issue of user's control at center stage, in this sense, provides stronger means to counteract the potential threats and risks that deception entails in the context of Artificial Sociality.",
    "Another implication of Artificial Sociality technologies is related, indeed, to the issue of human control in the experience of communicating and interacting with AI.",
    "This is central to the approach called Human-Centered Artificial Intelligence (HCAI) championed among others by Shneiderman (2022).",
    "HCAI proposes that it is possible to have high levels of automation and high levels of human control at the same time.",
    "Against the widely held tenet in Human-Computer Interaction that increased automation corresponds to lower level of human control (Sheridan, 1992), Shneiderman points to mature technologies such as elevators, cameras, and home appliances, which provide high levels of automation but also give users control to accomplish their tasks."
  ],
